.TH "scsi_add_lun" 9 "scsi_add_lun" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_add_lun \- allocate and fully initialze a scsi_device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scsi_add_lun
.BI "(struct scsi_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *inq_result "  ","
.BI "blist_flags_t *bflags "  ","
.BI "int async "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
holds information to be stored in the new scsi_device
.IP "inq_result" 12
holds the result of a previous INQUIRY to the LUN
.IP "bflags" 12
black/white list flag
.IP "async" 12
1 if this device is being scanned asynchronously
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initialize the scsi_device \fIsdev\fP.  Optionally set fields based
on values in *\fIbflags\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
SCSI_SCAN_NO_RESPONSE: could not allocate or setup a scsi_device
SCSI_SCAN_LUN_PRESENT: a new scsi_device was allocated and initialized
